I"\<p>The Doctrine of Double Effect argues that causing harm as an intended side effect is <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/responsibility-is-multidimensional">more permissible</a> than causing harm as a primary goal. This framework allows one to coherently accept self-driving cars occasionally resulting causing casualties, while simultaneously rejecting autonomous weapons designed specifically to kill. This perspective might support reasoning about <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memetic-psychotherapy-is-morally-ambiguous">the moral ambiguity of memetic psychotherapy</a>.</p>
